walk in the spirit and you shall not

256
00:12:39,359 --> 00:12:40,799
fulfill the lust of the flesh.

257
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:43,679
He doesn't make us walk in the spirit though.

258
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,640
He tells us to be filled with the spirit

259
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,119
but he doesn't make us be filled with the spirit.

260
00:12:48,119 --> 00:12:50,159
You can make a decision every day of your life

261
00:12:50,159 --> 00:12:51,940
to be filled with self.

262
00:12:51,940 --> 00:12:53,840
In fact, in the same text of scripture

263
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,599
in Galatians chapter number five,

264
00:12:55,599 --> 00:12:57,219
when the Bible provides for us

265
00:12:57,219 --> 00:12:58,799
what the fruit of the spirit is,

266
00:12:58,799 --> 00:13:01,799
we find in the preceding verses that God lays out

267
00:13:01,799 --> 00:13:04,859
what the works of the flesh are

268
00:13:04,859 --> 00:13:07,460
and he tells us, here's how they're manifest

269
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:09,820
and you begin to see all sorts of evil

270
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:12,580
and terrible things in these characteristics

271
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:14,380
and the reality this evening is that

272
00:13:14,380 --> 00:13:19,099
there's a possibility that some of God's people

273
00:13:19,099 --> 00:13:20,380
have lost their joy.

274
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,020
We begin to evaluate our own lives,

275
00:13:23,020 --> 00:13:26,179
examine our own lives and look at what the psalmist says

276
00:13:26,179 --> 00:13:27,900
in Psalm four in verse number seven,

277
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:32,460
thou has put gladness in my heart.

278
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:36,299
And I wonder this evening, could you say as the psalmist,

279
00:13:36,299 --> 00:13:40,559
thou has put gladness in my heart that I have that joy.

280
00:13:40,559 --> 00:13:42,780
Could you say as that little song goes

281
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:45,020
that we sing with the kids in Sunday school

282
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:48,340
and in junior church and in vacation Bible school,

283
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:53,340
Jesus gave it to me and nothing shall destroy it.

284
00:13:54,460 --> 00:13:55,299
Think about that.

285
00:13:55,299 --> 00:13:57,659
That's a powerful little statement in that song.

286
00:13:58,580 --> 00:14:03,580
Joyful people are praising people, amen?

287
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:06,099
Because if you have joy, you're gonna rejoice.

288
00:14:06,099 --> 00:14:09,260
The outworking of joy is rejoicing

289
00:14:09,260 --> 00:14:14,260
and therefore joyful people are praising people.

290
00:14:14,739 --> 00:14:18,020
Can I tell you this evening, we have much to give thanks for.

291
00:14:18,020 --> 00:14:20,900
We have so much to be thankful for.

292
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,460
I know that on Wednesday evening this past week,

293
00:14:23,460 --> 00:14:26,940
I preached that message, my cup runneth over

294
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:29,419
and someone commented to me this morning,

295
00:14:29,419 --> 00:14:30,859
I've been thinking about that phrase

296
00:14:30,859 --> 00:14:32,859
throughout the last several days since Wednesday,

297
00:14:32,859 --> 00:14:34,659
my cup runneth over.

298
00:14:34,659 --> 00:14:36,659
Oh, what a great phrase to be mindful of

299
00:14:36,659 --> 00:14:39,080
and to be thinking and meditating upon why,

300
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:42,659
because truly my cup runneth over.

301
00:14:42,659 --> 00:14:45,219
My God daily loadeth me with benefits.

302
00:14:45,219 --> 00:14:48,179
He's been so good to us.

303
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:51,679
We find that joyful people are praising people.

304
00:14:51,679 --> 00:14:52,520
Let me say this,

305
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:56,580
joyful people are pleasant people to be with, amen?

306
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,940
This is a really simple practical truth, isn't it?

307
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:03,559
But joyful people are pleasant to be around, amen?

308
00:15:03,559 --> 00:15:05,419
You like to be around joyful people?

309
00:15:06,619 --> 00:15:08,780
Raise your hand if you wanna be around joyful people.

310
00:15:08,780 --> 00:15:10,099
If you don't raise your hand, you're crazy,

311
00:15:10,099 --> 00:15:11,539
you need some help, amen?

312
00:15:11,539 --> 00:15:14,479
I'll try to sign you up for somebody to help you later,

313
00:15:14,479 --> 00:15:17,719
but if you wanna be around miserable complaining people,

314
00:15:17,719 --> 00:15:19,739
something's just not right.

315
00:15:19,739 --> 00:15:21,119
You understand what I'm saying?

316
00:15:21,119 --> 00:15:22,940
You get into a place and all of a sudden,

317
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:26,000
it's just miserable people and complaining people

318
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,080
and you're like, what is going on?

319
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,840
It's that old Eeyore syndrome, right?

320
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,479
Oh, bother.

321
00:15:33,479 --> 00:15:38,479
Like just everything's just, no man, we're going to heaven.

322
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,039
Jesus is my savior.

323
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:40,859
He loves me.

324
00:15:40,859 --> 00:15:42,520
He's given me all of these things.

325
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:43,520
I have a Bible.

326
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,039
I have the Holy Spirit that indwells me.

327
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:47,280
He's given me joy.

328
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:52,280
And David, he says, thou has put gladness in my heart.

329
00:15:53,359 --> 00:15:54,799
So I wonder this evening,

330
00:15:54,799 --> 00:15:56,500
again, we just have a few minutes,

331
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:58,479
but how's your joy?

332
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,080
Let me ask it this way.

333
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:05,599
Is it evident to those around you

334
00:16:05,599 --> 00:16:10,380
that the Lord hath put gladness in your heart?

335
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:12,400
Here's what I truly believe.

336
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:16,559
I believe that when we have joy,

337
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:18,880
when we have gladness,

338
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,799
that other people are gonna know that.

339
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,679
You can't hide it.

340
00:16:23,679 --> 00:16:27,320
Listen, what's on the inside comes out, amen?

341
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,080
And if you're filled with the Spirit

342
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,719
and you have that joy

343
00:16:30,719 --> 00:16:33,280
and you have that perspective that David speaks of,

344
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:35,340
thou has put gladness in my heart.

345
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:37,840
Listen, those people that you come in contact with,

346
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,679
they're gonna say, man, look at this person.

347
00:16:39,679 --> 00:16:41,460
They just have joy.

348
00:16:42,559 --> 00:16:44,640
Then someone might say, how do you have the joy?

349
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,080
I mean, how is it that you just seem

350
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:49,239
to always be glad and joyful?

351
00:16:49,239 --> 00:16:52,700
Listen, it's because of what my Lord has done for me.

352
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:56,719
Any of us can complain about anything.

353
00:16:56,719 --> 00:16:58,320
Listen, there's a lot going on in our world

354
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,979
that we can complain about.

355
00:16:59,979 --> 00:17:02,280
You can go down to the market,

356
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,200
you can go down to Costco

357
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:05,719
and you can find some people to complain with.

358
00:17:05,719 --> 00:17:07,680
You know what I'm saying?

359
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:09,540
I tried to find a parking spot there yesterday.

360
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:11,199
I'm sure that I could have found some people

361
00:17:11,199 --> 00:17:13,359
to complain with about trying to find a parking spot

362
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:15,400
on a Saturday at Costco.

363
00:17:16,959 --> 00:17:17,979
But it's okay.

364
00:17:18,979 --> 00:17:21,979
Thou has put gladness in my heart.

365
00:17:25,619 --> 00:17:27,140
It is God that gives it.

366
00:17:28,180 --> 00:17:33,020
So often we try to find that joy in other things.

367
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:35,420
Sometimes we try to find joy in people.

368
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:37,260
People will disappoint you.

369
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,540
Have you found that out?

370
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,660
Sometimes we try to put joy in maybe the things

371
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:46,739
that we have, the position that we hold.

372
00:17:46,739 --> 00:17:51,219
Listen, all those things are fading, just passing by.

373
00:17:51,219 --> 00:17:53,739
We sang to start the service this evening,

374
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:58,300
Jesus never changes, yesterday, today and forever.

375
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:01,579
And when I understand that He is my joy

376
00:18:01,579 --> 00:18:05,140
and that He hath put gladness in my heart,

377
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:09,219
then I live as an individual that is rejoicing,

378
00:18:09,219 --> 00:18:13,380
that's praising someone that others wanna be around.

379
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:14,219
Why?

380
00:18:14,219 --> 00:18:17,780
Because joyful people are pleasant people to be around.

381
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:19,420
They really are.

382
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:22,500
And so this evening, just a simple brief challenge.

383
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,020
How's our joy?

384
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:24,859
How's our joy?

385
00:18:25,739 --> 00:18:29,180
Say, man, I've been, I just feel like I've lost my joy.

386
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:32,180
In fact, Brother Mershon, a number of years ago,

387
00:18:32,180 --> 00:18:36,140
wrote an article that he titled Joy Thieves.

388
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:38,500
What is it that steals our joy?

389
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,540
And I said this as I looked at there at John 16,

390
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,619
something that we have to forfeit.

391
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:45,780
No man taketh it from you, we have to forfeit it.

392
00:18:46,619 --> 00:18:48,859
And here's the reality this evening.

393
00:18:48,859 --> 00:18:51,420
The world needs to see some of God's people

394
00:18:51,420 --> 00:18:56,020
being filled with the Spirit of God and having joy.

395
00:18:56,859 --> 00:18:59,540
Having joy, gladness.

396
00:18:59,540 --> 00:19:04,540
David says, thou hast put gladness in my heart.

397
00:19:04,579 --> 00:19:06,180
How's our joy?

398
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,540
How's our joy?

399
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:10,780
Is it coming out through rejoicing, we're praising?

400
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:12,420
Do other people see it?

401
00:19:13,219 --> 00:19:14,060
Just a simple thought this evening,

402
00:19:14,060 --> 00:19:16,180
but I hope as we go throughout this week

403
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:19,739
that we'll be mindful that we're to be a joyful people,

404
00:19:19,739 --> 00:19:20,739
a praising people.

405
00:19:20,739 --> 00:19:21,579
Let's pray.

406
00:19:21,579 --> 00:19:22,780
Father, we love you.

407
00:19:22,780 --> 00:19:24,579
We thank you for loving us.

408
00:19:24,579 --> 00:19:26,459
Thank you for each song that we had the opportunity

409
00:19:26,459 --> 00:19:27,699
to sing this evening.

410
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:30,540
And thank you for the messages that we received

411
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:33,339
through those great hymns of the faith.

412
00:19:34,219 --> 00:19:37,140
Being reminded of the fact that you're coming again

413
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:39,719
and being reminded of the fact that you can do anything

414
00:19:39,719 --> 00:19:42,560
and being reminded of the fact that you died for us

415
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,920
and that you rose conquering sin, death, and the grave,

416
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,479
that you live forevermore.

417
00:19:46,479 --> 00:19:49,979
I mean, so many wonderful lessons and messages

418
00:19:49,979 --> 00:19:51,339
that we were able to receive

419
00:19:51,339 --> 00:19:53,760
through those songs this evening.

420
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,640
And now as we take just a few moments

421
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:59,359
to look at this statement of the psalmist in Psalm four,

422
00:19:59,359 --> 00:20:02,260
God, would you help us to evaluate our lives?

423
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:08,560
Can we honestly say thou hast put gladness in my heart?

424
00:20:09,239 --> 00:20:11,400
Am I a joyful person?

425
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,599
Do I have the fruit of the spirit

426
00:20:13,599 --> 00:20:15,640
as evidenced in my life?

427
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:22,180
Do others recognize that I have that joy that you've given?

428
00:20:24,079 --> 00:20:26,479
I pray, Father, that if we've come to the place

429
00:20:26,479 --> 00:20:29,400
where we've kind of lost our joy,

430
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,560
God, would you help us to get it right this evening?

431
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,520
Lord, help us to change our perspective.

432
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:35,719
Lord, help us to see you for who you are.

433
00:20:35,719 --> 00:20:39,280
Lord, help us to receive what you have for us

434
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,760
and to be able to be in that place

435
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:43,199
where we could say, as David did,

436
00:20:43,199 --> 00:20:45,000
thou hast put gladness in my heart.

437
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,839
Help us to change our perspective.

438
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,880
I pray, God, that you'd work in hearts and lives

439
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,760
as only you can.

440
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,880
I pray that decisions would be made that would please thee.

441
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,839
Well, thank you for it.

442
00:20:55,839 --> 00:20:56,839
In Christ's name we pray.

443
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:57,719
Would you stand with me?

444
00:20:57,719 --> 00:20:58,800
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

445
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,599
Just a brief invitation this evening.

446
00:21:02,599 --> 00:21:06,119
Simple thought, thou hast put gladness in my heart.

447
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:08,800
More, he says, these people,

448
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,199
their corn and their wine increased,

449
00:21:11,199 --> 00:21:13,800
but God, the gladness, the joy that you gave me

450
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,280
is more than that.

451
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,680
How's your joy this evening?

452
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:18,800
As Kimberly plays, the altar is open.

